         <lg type="sonnet">
            <head>Complaint of a <choice><orig>louer</orig><reg>lover</reg></choice> rebuked.</head>
            <l>Love that liveth and reigneth in my thought,</l>
            <l>That built his <choice><orig>ſeat</orig><reg>seat</reg></choice> within my <choice><orig>captiue</orig><reg>captive</reg></choice> <choice><orig>breſt</orig><reg>brest</reg></choice>,</l>
            <l>Clad in the armes, wherin with me he fought,</l>
            <l>Oft in my face he doth his banner <choice><orig>reſt</orig><reg>rest</reg></choice>.</l>
            <l>She, that in me taught to <choice><orig>loue</orig><reg>love</reg></choice>, and <choice><orig>ſuffer</orig><reg>suffer</reg></choice> payne,</l>
            <l>My doutfull hope, and eke my hote <choice><orig>deſyre</orig><reg>desyre</reg></choice>,</l>
            <l>With <choice><orig>ſhamefaſt</orig><reg>shamefast</reg></choice> cloke to <choice><orig>ſhadowe</orig><reg>shadowe</reg></choice> and refraine,</l>
            <l>Her <choice><orig>ſmilyng</orig><reg>smilying</reg></choice> grace <choice><orig>conuerteth</orig><reg>converteth</reg></choice> <choice><orig>ſtraight</orig><reg>straight</reg></choice> to yre.</l>
            <l>And cowarde <choice><orig>Loue</orig><reg>Love</reg></choice> then to the hart apace</l>
            <l>Taketh his flight, whereas he lurkes, and plaines</l>
            <l>His <choice><orig>purpoſe</orig><reg>purpose</reg></choice> <choice><orig>loſt</orig><reg>lost</reg></choice>, and darenot <choice><orig>ſhewe</orig><reg>shewe</reg></choice> his face.</l>
            <l>For my lordes gilt thus <choice><orig>faultleſſ</orig><reg>faultless</reg></choice> byde I paynes.</l>
            <l>Yet from my lorde <choice><orig>ſhall</orig><reg>shall</reg></choice> not my foote <choice><orig>remoue</orig><reg>remove</reg></choice>,</l>
            <l>Swete is his death, that takes his end by <choice><orig>loue</orig><reg>love</reg></choice>.</l>
         </lg>
         <note type="translation" resp="#jawalsh">Translation of <title rendition="#i">Rvf 140</title>  by Henry Howard, Earl of Surrey (1517?–1547), from <title rendition="#i">Tottel’s Miscellany</title> (1557).</note>
